Name: UCSB
Description: A great university located along the California coast

Name: Poles
Description: Surf spot located east of Campus point. Great conditions on short period west swell with minimal wind

Name: Campus Point
Description: Surf spot iconic for freshman surfers attending UCSB. Great on big west swells on a mid tide.

Name: Depressions
Description: Surf Spot just west of Campus point denoted by a depressed cliffside along the break, hence the name "Depressions"

Name: Devereux Point
Description: Classic surf spot great for longboarding with slow & soft peeling waves. Watch for bubbles coming from the ground

Name: Sands
Description: More advanced surf spot on the other side of Coal & Oil point. Picks up variety of swells, good on mid tide.
